Step#1 start a listner on the attacking machine:
>>> nc -lvnp <port>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step2# In the listner use:
>>> python -c 'import pty;pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
    (Note that .. some targets might need diffrent python versions which can be , python , python2 or python3)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step3# use:
>>> export TERM=xterm
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step4# press:
>>> Ctrl + z
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step5# use:
>>> stty raw -echo; fg
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step6# then write this :
>>>> reset 
......................................................................................................................
the shell would start with freedom to do everything.

